        h5 As a designer, I research and plan.  I imagine and create. I think broadly as well as granularly. 
        //- p As much as possible, I do not allow technology to dictate the message or story of a design. Instead, I find a way to make the technology work for the design. That’s the beauty of having one foot in the creative world and the other in development. I can ask the 
        //-   i 
        //-     b what if&nbsp;
        //-   |  questions in design and then write the code that answers the questions. 
        p In my approach to design, I prioritize ensuring that technology enhances rather than dictates the message or narrative. By seamlessly integrating technology into the design process, I bridge the gap between creativity and development. This dual perspective allows me to explore the possibilities in design through "what if" inquiries and subsequently craft code that brings those concepts to life.
